## Now — blockers + actively-in-flight

- **Phase 2d — BlockBook** (IBD started on carson 2026-04-24, 8-18h). Once in sync: add `BLOCKBOOK_URL=http://127.0.0.1:9131` to `/etc/tokenstork/env`; enable `sync-enrich.timer` + `sync-verify.timer`; the `—` placeholders for holder count / live UTXOs / live NFTs / fully-burned count flip to real data. Unblocks items below marked *(blocked on BlockBook)*.
- **Verify + close [#14](https://github.com/Panmoni/tokenstork/issues/14) (XLV max-supply miscount)** post-BlockBook. Pull XLV's category hex, run `enrich` one-shot, confirm `current_supply` matches post-burn total (~61000.57996200 as of 2024-09-09, modulo burns since). *(blocked on BlockBook)*
- **Verify sparklines populate end-to-end ~2026-05-01** (one week post-Phase-4f deploy, 2026-04-24). Expected: 317 Cauldron listings × ~6 points/day × 7 days ≈ 13,000+ rows in `token_price_history`. Runbook:
  ```
  sudo -u bchn psql -d tokenstork -c "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM token_price_history;"
  sudo -u bchn psql -d tokenstork -c "SELECT last_cauldron_run_at, now() - last_cauldron_run_at AS staleness FROM sync_state WHERE id = 1;"
  ```
  UI smoke at <https://tokenstork.com/>: sparklines colored, 1h/24h/7d columns populated, MetricsBar shows real Total TVL.

