## Next — short list, roughly in order

- **Operational hardening** — `pg_dump` nightly timer with 7-daily / 4-weekly retention + weekly offsite ship (Backblaze B2 or Hetzner Storage Box, ~€1/mo); UptimeRobot free-tier on `/api/tokens?limit=1`; tail-staleness watchdog timer using `sync_state.last_tail_run_at`; weekly Netcup snapshot toggle.
- **Icon safety pipeline — CSAM + NSFW gating** for every BCMR image. Supersedes the earlier "transcode worker" idea. Default-deny: no image byte reaches a visitor until scanned + marked `cleared`; otherwise render the SVG placeholder. Cloudflare CSAM Scanning Tool + cloud NSFW API (GCV SafeSearch or AWS Rekognition, ~$20 one-shot + <$5/mo), transcode to static WebP, serve from `/var/lib/tokenstork/icons/<sha256>.webp` via Caddy. New `icon_moderation` + `icon_url_scan` tables. Full design in the plan doc. Legal: mandatory NCMEC reporting under 18 U.S.C. § 2258A; CF's tool auto-files. Ship **before** wallet login.
- **Watchlist (anonymous, localStorage first)** — star button on token cards + detail page; persists category IDs to `localStorage['tokenstork:watchlist']`. New `/watchlist` route reads IDs and routes through existing `TokenGrid` + a `?ids=<csv>` loader. Header shows "Watchlist (N)" when non-empty. Foundation for wallet-login portfolio.
- **Fex.cash on-chain indexer** (plan + recon landed at [docs/fex-plan.md](docs/fex-plan.md)). New `sync-fex` Rust worker modelled on `sync-cauldron`, scans asset P2SH `a9142b389120e9c741fbc5dbcd51fc4170d6640b9d3687` via `scantxoutset`. 10 pools, 15.14 BCH total. ~1.25 days. Ship after BlockBook so the directory isn't fighting two rollouts. Reuses `token_venue_listings` with `venue='fex'`.
- **Cross-venue arbitrage scanner** — new `/arbitrage` page. For categories with BOTH `token_venue_listings(venue='cauldron')` AND open `tapswap_offers`, compute the spread after fees (Cauldron ~0.3%, Tapswap 3%, mining-fee buffer, Cauldron slippage vs TVL). Surface spreads >2%. Pure SQL (CTE joining the two tables), no new worker.
- **Expanded `/stats` page** — pick 3-5 from: top gainers/losers 24h, largest TVL movers 24h, most-listed on Tapswap, ecosystem growth curve (genesis_time weekly buckets), metadata completeness %, decimals distribution, active minting count, supply-bracket distribution, Cauldron × Tapswap Venn, 30-day ecosystem TVL sparkline, genesis-block histogram. My pick: gainers/losers + growth curve + venue Venn + metadata completeness + active minting. ~1 day.
- **Long-horizon charts + per-day volume on token detail page** — replace the inline 7-day sparkline with a real line chart (native SVG, no heavy JS libs) + range toggles 24h/7d/30d/90d/1y/all. Second series: per-day volume derived from consecutive `token_price_history` TVL deltas. Data source already accumulating since Phase 4f.
- **Holder distribution + concentration metrics** on the token detail page — top 10 holders bar chart, Gini, Herfindahl, "top-10 hold X%" headline. *(blocked on BlockBook — `token_holders` empty until enrichment runs.)*
- **Runbook** — collect failure-mode recipes into `docs/runbook.md` for the tired 3am self.

---

## Later — wallet login + the features that stack on it

- **BCH wallet login** — `/api/auth/challenge` → wallet signs canonical message → `/api/auth/verify` recovers the address (via libauth ECDSA). Session cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict, 30-day). Schema: `users(cashaddr PK)`, `auth_challenges(nonce PK, expires_at)`, `sessions(id PK, cashaddr FK)`. Hard constraint: wallet signing only — no email/password, no OAuth, no magic links. Day-one UX is a `/login` page with "paste (cashaddr, signature)" for universal wallet support; Paytaca Connect / WalletConnect later. On first login, prompt to merge localStorage watchlist into `user_watchlist`. Full heavy-duty 3-pass review before ship.
- **User watchlist + portfolio** (unlocks after wallet login): `user_watchlist` cross-device; later `user_portfolio` with manual buy entries OR derive from on-chain holdings at the linked address via BlockBook.
- **CSV export** on `/api/tokens` (`?format=csv`) and a new `/api/tokens/<cat>/history`. Power-user credibility at couple-of-hours cost.
- **Per-user price alerts** (wallet-delivered notification via the wallet's messaging layer, or optional email-as-metadata-only; never used for login).
- **Personal annotations** on tokens ("this one was the rug").

