## Feature roadmap

### 0.1.0 — ecosystem dashboard maturity
- BlockBook-driven enrichment live (holder counts, live UTXOs, live NFTs, fully-burned).
- Icon safety pipeline live.
- Watchlist (anonymous) live.
- Fex indexer live.
- Arbitrage scanner live.
- `/stats` expanded.
- Operational hardening live.

### 0.2.0 — accounts + persistence
- BCH wallet login.
- User watchlist + portfolio.
- CSV export + history endpoint.
- Long-horizon charts + volume on token detail page.
- Holder distribution + concentration on token detail page.

### 0.3.0 — ecosystem leaderboards (tokenaut.cash-inspired)
- `/defi` — aggregate BCH locked across covenant families (Cauldron + AnyHedge + Moria + BCH Bull + BCH Guru + Badgers + Emerald DAO + BCH PUMP). Headline "Total BCH locked in DeFi". Columns: name, icon, category, live TVL (BCH + USD), status, active_contracts, total_contract_txs, 7-day Δ%, tx velocity. Covenant script-family registry is ~1 week of reverse-engineering across top 8 projects.
- `/nft` — NFT collections leaderboard: minted/max_supply, mint_price, mint_revenue, floor_price, holders, last_mint, mints_7d. Floor derived from Cauldron NFT-commitment pools + Tapswap P2P asks. Differentiators Tokenaut cannot match: holder count, Gini, last-mint time, mints_7d, burn events, live floor.
- Projects/Issuers layer — new `projects` + `token_project` tables. Seed from hand-curated `db/seed/projects.json` (~30 entries). Directory gains `?category=forwards` chip; token detail gains "Issued by …".
- Category maturity badge — `active / dormant (no on-chain activity in 90d) / burned-out / abandoned`.
- Launch-date first-class: "Minted May 19, 2023" on cards + sort-by-age.
- Filter chips on directory backed by category / status / use-case.
- Repo badge (BCMR `uris.repo`/`uris.github` → GitHub link-badge).
- Wallet-support badges ("Listed in Zapit / Paytaca / Cashonize / Electron Cash", periodic scrape).

### 0.4.0 — content + integrations
- Integrate TokenStokRegistry + regular OTR sync.
- CRC20 tab ([reference](https://gitlab.com/0353F40E/crc20-to-bcmr/-/blob/master/bcmr/bitcoin-cash-metadata-registry.json?ref_type=heads), [devs channel](https://t.me/cashtoken_devs/13114)).
- Fees in header — last-block `fee_satoshis / transaction_count` via Chaingraph, or equivalent off BCHN direct.
- Additional HelloBar/metrics API calls (crypto FGI via [cryptocompare](https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/documentation), etc.).
- Endpoint for getting NFTs by commitment ([paytaca PR #25](https://github.com/paytaca/bcmr-indexer/pull/25)).
- Events/airdrops page (curator-maintained JSON of upcoming mints / airdrops / flipstarters tied to categories).
- Header transparency widget — sync lag (head vs tip) + BlockBook uptime.

### 0.5.0 — performance + a11y
- Lighthouse pass. Responsive images ([offscreen-images](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/offscreen-images/)), CLS ([optimize-cls](https://web.dev/articles/optimize-cls)), CSP/XSS hardening ([csp-xss](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/best-practices/csp-xss/)).
- Parallelize page loads: streaming, suspense, islands.
- Comprehensive error-checking + tests.
- A11y sweep: aria labels, keyboard nav, screen-reader trend summaries.
- Custom site themes.
- Responsive breakpoint audit.
- Ensure strong search-engine uptake.

### 0.7.0 — token creation + wallet integration
- WalletConnect 2 integration.
- Create FTs and NFTs from the UI.
- Historical price graphs.
- Token management tools (metadata updates, dividends, mass distribution, airdrops, secure authbase).
- Updates feed when tokens update their BCMR data.
- Badges for tokens updated recently + listed in various BCMR registries (e.g. otr.cash).

### 0.9.0 — BCMR identity + surrounding chain data
- BCMR identities for people + organizations.
- Other BCH chain data surfaced throughout.

### 1.0.0 — ICOs + trading
- Create ICOs with oversight + milestone-gated releases; investor voting on payments or pro-rata returns; community update tools.
- Trading volume tracking.
- ICOs → stock exchange?

### 1.5.0 — real-world contracts
- Additional on-chain products, e.g. annuities ([example](https://unspent.app/contract?opReturn=6a047574786f0141010102f00317a914ae83c90909bf710ef2d948ebf6f957a9219f549c8703884e0b02b00417a914fc133e739da7ad80cb97c254cc6499c761e4b88287&network=mainnet)).
- Outreach to ~20 companies for RWA tokenization partnerships on CashTokens.
- Content on tokenization use cases, connected to BCH solutions ([brickken](https://www.brickken.com/use-cases)). Build tools + demos.

### 2.0.0
- Social features.

